We also analyzed our results in terms of the dispersion relation $\omega(q)$.
The dispersion relation can be obtained from the density of states (DOS), $D(\omega)$, via the standard relation 
$D(\omega)d\omega=\frac{1}{4\pi^{2}}q^{2}dq$.
The results are plotted in Fig.2 of this appendix. 
